is up to you.

25
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,960
But I think you'd better
give up now, Ms. Nana.

26
00:03:56,520 --> 00:04:00,240
Because Tharn doesn't like…

27
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:03,880
your type.

28
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:07,200
Where's Mr. Tharn? I'm going to call him.

29
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,960
I'm warning you for your own sake.

30
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,680
Because you'll never get
what you're hoping for.

31
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,960
It's not too late to change your mind now.

32
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:21,640
Because Tharn…

33
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,120
likes men.

34
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:28,800
And not just any type of man.

35
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:32,280
He only likes a man like me.

36
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,120
If you'll excuse me.

37
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:40,480
I've been out for too long.
Tharn's probably missing me.

38
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:45,280
As for you, Ms. Nana.
Have a safe trip home.

39
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:50,640
It's not safe for a fragile woman
to come looking for a man.

40
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,360
Just a friendly warning.

41
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:11,600
Have you been driven mad by anger?
Why are you laughing?

42
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,000
Seriously…

43
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:17,640
I knew what you'd do.

44
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,200
What did you think I'd do?

45
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:26,400
