104
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:47,000
But I think my brother got too excited.

105
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:52,840
How is it?

106
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:56,080
Does your heart ache hearing about this?

107
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,160
Nope.

108
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:02,720
Because I've got someone of my own.

109
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:07,600
Tharn's a brother I cherish.
Good memories from the past, nothing more.

110
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:11,840
I'm happy that you've given up on him.

111
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:16,960
And I'm even happier
that you're serious about someone.

112
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:23,200
Now I can stop worrying about you bugging
my brother and sister-in-law again.

113
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:27,240
Come on, don't worry.
I won't bug them anymore.

114
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,400
They've been in love for seven years.
That's a long time already.

115
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:35,600
Come on, let's continue the game.
Quick, grab your phone. Come on.

116
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,760
Where were we?

117
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,440
What are you doing?

118
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,120
Working.

119
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,000
Hello.

120
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:08,600
<i>Hello, Type.</i>
<i>Have you seen that woman's IG post?</i>

121
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:13,000
-What woman?
<i>-The one who was after Tharn.</i>

122
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,400
What about her?

123
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:21,200
<i>Stop asking. Go check it out. Hurry.</i>

124
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,040
Okay.

125
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:30,440
THANK YOU FOR THE PAST TWO YEARS.
I'VE LEARNED A LOT HERE.

126
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:35,000
THANK YOU, WONDERFUL COLLEAGUES
AND PERFECT BOSS. THANK YOU.

127
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:39,520
I'LL VISIT YOU GUYS SOMETIME. LOVE.

128
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,400
WHY DID YOU QUIT?

129
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:47,200
HOW COULD I STAY?
COULDN'T GET THE OLDER ONE.

130
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:49,880
YOUNGER ONE IGNORES ME. SO EMBARRASSED.

131
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:11,880
THANK YOU FOR BEING SO UNDERSTANDING.

132
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:21,720
-Techno.
-Go away. This is important.

133
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:26,480
-Techno.
-Hey, Tharn! What's up, dude?

134
00:12:26,560 --> 00:12:28,480
It's been a while.

135
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,400
-How are you?
-I'm doing well.

136
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:33,320
I'm thinking of buying rings today.

137
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:37,200
I'll pick out a few of them for myself
as accessories.

138
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,400
God damn it!
You act like nothing happened.

139
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,360
What's wrong?

140
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:44,960
Who was that woman?

141
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:49,480
If Type finds out you're cheating,
you'll be dead meat.

142
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,240
You know that, right?

143
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,320
-Know what?
-It won't be a pretty sight.

144
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:57,200
And you know what? If he finds out…

145
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,480
he'll cut it off and feed it to the ducks.

146
00:13:01,560 --> 00:13:03,000
Come on.

147
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:07,120
Let's just say I didn't do anything…

148
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:11,400
that would cut Type off
from his daily needs.

149
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,440
Damn, his daily needs.

150
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:20,320
Seriously, dude.
Were you born a cocky bastard?

151
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,520
-Tell me what happened?
-Nothing happened.

152
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:26,720
But it's a good thing you came here.

153
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:33,720
-I need your help.
-I've got no money.

154
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,000
It's not about money.

155
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:40,640
-Help make my boyfriend jealous.
-Are you crazy?

156
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,800
I'm not.

157
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:44,000
Why would you get yourself into trouble?

158
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:47,280
-Please, Techno.
-No, I won't do it.

159
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,640
I'll buy you a meal.

160
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:52,520
Tell me the first plan. I'm all ears.

161
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:54,760
I've been on your side this whole time.

162
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:57,640
Trust me, I won't fail you.

163
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,680
You'll be so impressed.

164
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,400
What are you looking at?

165
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:09,360
There's something on your face.

166
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,360
-My face?
-Yeah, there.

167
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,000
It's gone.

168
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:27,000
There you are, Type.

169
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:29,400
I've been waiting for you.

170
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,520
I bought some snacks for you.

171
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,320
I can't accept them.

172
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,960
Please, take them.
I really wanna apologize to you.

173
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,520
Please.

174
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,520
If you don't take them,
I've got to throw them away.

175
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:51,920
Look.

176
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:55,560
I bought a lot for the doctors and nurses.

177
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,160
Okay.

178
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,280
Thank you very much.

179
00:15:03,880 --> 00:15:05,760
But you don't need to do this again.

180
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,200
You see, I--

181
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,160
don't want to trouble you.

182
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:11,920
Copy that.

183
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,280
Mr. Thiwat, the boss is asking for you.

184
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:19,520
What's the matter?

185
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,160
I don't know. What have you done?

186
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,840
I've got to go.

187
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,000
Okay.

188
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:35,600
Don't forget your PT appointment
next week.

189
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:38,440
-Okay.
-See you.

190
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,320
I refused your leave request.

191
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:06,960
You know many people take leave
during the long holiday.

192
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:11,920
And our department is short-staffed,
so you'll have to come in to work.

193
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:14,560
But I've referred all my work plans
to Ms. Teng.

194
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:19,640
Besides, I applied for leave
a long time ago.

195
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,560
I'm telling you I won't grant it.

196
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:25,480
Why, sir?

197
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,640
We're short-staffed.

198
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,560
Or do you insist on taking leave…

199
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,640
while other people
devote their time to work?

200
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:38,680
Are you trying to force me, sir?

201
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:44,760
Thiwat, you'd better watch what you say.

202
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:49,800
Don't forget that I am your superior.

203
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,360
Yes, sir.

204
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:04,920
